Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Thinly slice the @Portobello Mushrooms{2}. Peel and grate
the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the mushroom to the pan
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring often, until golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of oil to the pan if needed.

Once the mushrooms are cooked, stir in the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}.

While the mushrooms are cooking, drain and tear the @mozzarella{1} into small chunks.
Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Meanwhile, in a small #bowl{}, combine the @fresh pesto{50%g}
and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} for the pesto, then set aside.

Put the @plain naans{2} onto a large #baking tray{}. Use the back of a #spoon{} to spread
the pesto mixture evenly all over the base of each naan, leaving a 1cm border around the edge.

Lay the garlicky mushrooms onto the naanizzas. Scatter over the mozzarella.

Bake the Naanizzas on the top shelf of your oven until the cheese has melted and is
bubbly and the base is crisp, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @wild rocket{40} and baby plum tomatoes into a bowl. Season with salt and
pepper, mix together then set aside.

Once everything is cooked, serve the naanizzas topped with the salad and with a drizzle
of the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} all over. Enjoy!